  "title": "Admin Assistant",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>1) Liaise with clients on account receivables</p>\n<p>2) Send and update on daily queries</p>\n<p>3) Update daily payment files and account placement</p>\n<p>4) Prepare monthly invoicing and reconciliation of accounts</p>\n<p>5) Generation of reports</p>\n<p>6) Assist and review cases for reporting</p>\n<p>7) Manage and monitor the accounts to ensure compliance to client’s requirements</p>\n<p>8) Other ad-hoc duties as and when required</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma/GCE ‘A’ Level/GCE ‘O’ Level/Higher Nitec Certificate/Nitec Certificate</li>\n  <li>1-3 years of relevant experience</li>\n  <li>Proficient in MS Office especially Excel</li>\n  <li>Working knowledge of V lookup/Pivot table</li>\n  <li>Meticulous and strong with numbers</li>\n  <li>Able to perform well within tight deadlines with minimum supervision</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Working hours:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>8.30am to 6.15pm (Monday to Thursday)</li>\n  <li>Friday: 8.15am to 6pm</li>\n  <li>5-day work week</li>\n  <li>Office hours</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Salary and Benefits:</strong></p>\n<p>-   Annual Leave/ Birthday Leave/ Childcare Leave/ Maternity Leave/Paternity Leave<br>\n-   Medical coverage provided</p>",
